  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 12 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 3 critical, 17 high, 7 medium, 12 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR) and Chişinău (RMO/LUKK); plus 17 other bases. 7 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is snow-related runway contamination risk, mist and low cloud base  — most notably around Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP), Vilnius (VNO/EYVI) and Bucharest Băneasa Aurel Vlaicu (BBU/LRBS). Network hotspots: Göteborg Landvetter (GOT/ESGG), Seve Ballesteros-Santander (SDR/LEXJ), Bergen Airport, Flesland (BGO/ENBR), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO) and 7 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, mist and cold‑temperature performance penalties. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Bergen Airport, Flesland (BGO/ENBR), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO) and 9 others.",
